    Note over Admin, DB: Flow 1: Platform Installation
    Admin->>OLM: Install rhods-operator (FBC catalog)
    OLM->>DSCI: Deploy operator, Admin creates DSCI CR
    DSCI->>DSCI: Create namespaces, NetworkPolicies, Auth
    DSCI->>Gateway: Create GatewayClass + Gateway
    DSCI->>KubeAuth: Deploy kube-auth-proxy
    DSCI->>EnvoyFilter: Create ext_authz filter
    Admin->>DSC: Create DataScienceCluster CR
    DSC->>Dashboard: Deploy Dashboard + plugins
    DSC->>KServe: Deploy KServe controller
    DSC->>DSPServer: Deploy DSP operator
    DSC->>NotebookCtrl: Deploy Notebook controller

    Note over Admin, DB: Flow 2: User Authentication (RHOAI 3.x)
    Admin->>Gateway: HTTPS request /dashboard
    Gateway->>EnvoyFilter: Route check
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeAuth: ext_authz (validate session)
    KubeAuth-->>EnvoyFilter: No valid session
    EnvoyFilter-->>Gateway: 302 Redirect
    Gateway-->>Admin: Redirect to OAuth
    Admin->>OAuth: Login (credentials)
    OAuth-->>Admin: Auth code redirect
    Admin->>KubeAuth: /oauth2/callback (auth code)
    KubeAuth->>OAuth: Exchange code for token
    OAuth-->>KubeAuth: Access token
    KubeAuth-->>Admin: Set session cookie, redirect
    Admin->>Gateway: HTTPS request (with cookie)
    Gateway->>EnvoyFilter: Route check
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeAuth: ext_authz (validate session)
    KubeAuth-->>EnvoyFilter: Valid: Bearer token injected
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeRBACProxy: Forward with Authorization header
    KubeRBACProxy->>KubeRBACProxy: SubjectAccessReview
    KubeRBACProxy->>Dashboard: Proxy to backend

    Note over Admin, DB: Flow 3: Model Inference (InferenceService)
    Admin->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>443/HTTPS
    Gateway->>EnvoyFilter: Route check
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeAuth: ext_authz
    KubeAuth-->>EnvoyFilter: Authorized
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeRBACProxy: Forward via HTTPRoute
    KubeRBACProxy->>Runtime: Proxy to runtime (8000/HTTP)
    Runtime->>Storage: Load model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443
    Storage-->>Runtime: Model data
    Runtime-->>KubeRBACProxy: Prediction response
    KubeRBACProxy-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Admin: JSON prediction result

    Note over Admin, DB: Flow 4: ML Pipeline Execution
    Admin->>Dashboard: Create pipeline run
    Dashboard->>DSPServer: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>8888/HTTP
    DSPServer->>ArgoWF: Create Workflow CR
    ArgoWF->>ArgoWF: Create step Pods
    ArgoWF->>MLMeta: Record metadata<br/>gRPC/8080
    MLMeta->>DB: Store metadata<br/>SQL/3306
    ArgoWF->>Storage: Store artifacts<br/>S3/443
    ArgoWF-->>DSPServer: Workflow complete
    DSPServer-->>Dashboard: Run results
    Dashboard-->>Admin: Display results

    Note over Admin, DB: Flow 5: Notebook/Workbench Session
    Admin->>Dashboard: Create Notebook CR
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Notebook CR created
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Create Pod, Service, HTTPRoute
    NotebookCtrl->>KubeRBACProxy: Inject kube-rbac-proxy sidecar
    Admin->>Gateway: Access workbench<br/>443/HTTPS
    Gateway->>EnvoyFilter: Route check
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeAuth: ext_authz
    KubeAuth-->>EnvoyFilter: Authorized
    EnvoyFilter->>KubeRBACProxy: Forward via HTTPRoute
    KubeRBACProxy->>Notebook: Proxy to JupyterLab<br/>8888/HTTP
    Notebook-->>Admin: Notebook UI
